The proposed threshold is too clever:

> median per-round process wall time > 1.5× bytes-generated / observed-token-rate

That tries to infer model time from output bytes, but `shelley.ts` prompts are dominated by input context, not just generated output. Queueing, tool boot, auth lookup, prompt ingestion, and model-side variance all get folded into the residual. It creates a false sense of precision.

Use a cruder but harder-to-game rule:

- Instrument current `codex exec`.
- Run 3 existing 3-round Codex-vs-Codex debates.
